sec.p:
Total RNA was extracted from cardiac tissues and cells using TRIzol® reagent, and RNA quality and concentration were assessed with a NanoDrop 2000 spectrophotometer, ensuring an OD260/280 ratio of 1.8–2.0. PCR primers were custom-designed and synthesized by Sangon Biotech Co., Ltd. Quantitative real-time PCR was performed on an ABI PRISM 7500 system using a SYBR Green I kit, with β-actin serving as the internal reference for normalization. Relative gene expression levels were calculated using the 2−ΔΔCt method, with all experiments conducted in triplicate. The primer sequences used are as follows:
DDX60:
Forward: 5ʹ-AGAAAAGACCCAGACCCCAG-3ʹ;
Reverse: 5ʹ-CGCCTTCATCGCTCTCTTTC-3ʹ.
Arl2:
Forward: 5ʹ-ACCCTCCTCATCTTTGCCAA-3ʹ;
Reverse: 5ʹ-TCGGCAGTAAAGACACGACT-3ʹ.
EIF4G1:
Forward: 5ʹ-GCACAGAATCTCAGCCTTCG-3ʹ;
Reverse: 5ʹ-AATACGGCTCCCCAGTTTCA-3ʹ.
β-actin:
Forward: 5ʹ-CCTCTATGCCAACACAGTGC-3ʹ;
Reverse: 5ʹ-CCTGCTTGCTGATCCACATC-3ʹ.
